msgs.text:
I prepared the exact repair package for the three gaps identified in the uploaded manuscript. 

The revisions:

- replace the unsupported cellular Stokes argument with a direct finite-word Heisenberg conjugation calculation;
- construct the involution-stabilized orbit cocycle and its correction functions \(m_c\) explicitly;
- eliminate the residual \(H^1(H,V^\vee)\) ambiguity rigorously;
- give the normalized Shapiro–corestriction calculation identifying the half-orbit graph class with the index-two Evens norm;
- add the relevant Evens, Kahn, and Kozlowski references. 

The revised source compiles cleanly to a 44-page PDF.

[Download the revised LaTeX source](sandbox:/mnt/data/q2_presentation_gap_closure.tex)

[Download the directly applicable patch](sandbox:/mnt/data/q2_presentation_gap_closure.patch)

[Download the compiled revised PDF](sandbox:/mnt/data/q2_presentation_gap_closure.pdf)

[Download the insertion and modification notes](sandbox:/mnt/data/q2_presentation_gap_closure_notes.md)

These edits close the three specific defects from my review. They are not, by themselves, an independent certification of every unchanged lemma elsewhere in the manuscript.
